{
  "title": "ISic001094. I.Sicily inscription 001094",
  "body": "<div id=\"editions\"><div class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Alessandra Rocchetti; edition source: <a href=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/Q2SBPG9F\">https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/Q2SBPG9F</a></div><div id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"grc\">  <div class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\"><span class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  <a id=\"al1-interpretive\"><!--0--></a><span class=\"linenumber\">1</span>[<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>] καισαρ<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">.</span> [<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>] <br id=\"al2-interpretive\"><span class=\"linenumber\">2</span>[<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span> α]υτοκρα[<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>] <br id=\"al3-interpretive\"><span class=\"linenumber\">3</span>[<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>]ου σεβα[<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>] <br id=\"al4-interpretive\"><span class=\"linenumber\">4</span>[<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>]σεπτικ[<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>] <br id=\"al5-interpretive\"><span class=\"linenumber\">5</span>[<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>]στραν κα[<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>] <br id=\"al6-interpretive\"><span class=\"linenumber\">6</span>[<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>] <span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">.</span>  <span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Φλαουιο\"><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Φλαουιο\"><span data-text=\"Φλαουιο\">Φλαουιο</span>[<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>]</span></span>  </span></div>  <p class=\"miniapp\"></p></div><div class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Alessandra Rocchetti; edition source: <a href=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/Q2SBPG9F\">https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/Q2SBPG9F</a></div><div id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"grc\"><div class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\"><span class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\"><a id=\"al1-diplomatic\"><!--0--></a><span class=\"linenumber\">1</span>[<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>]ΚΑΙΣΑΡ<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">·</span>[<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>]<br id=\"al2-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">2</span>[<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>.]ΥΤΟΚΡΑ[<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>]<br id=\"al3-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">3</span>[<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>]ΟΥΣΕΒΑ[<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>]<br id=\"al4-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">4</span>[<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>]ΣΕΠΤΙΚ[<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>]<br id=\"al5-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">5</span>[<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>]ΣΤΡΑΝΚΑ[<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>]<br id=\"al6-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">6</span>[<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>]<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">·</span><span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Φλαουιο\"><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Φλαουιο\"><span data-text=\"Φλαουιο\">ΦΛΑΟΥΙΟ</span>[<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>]</span></span></span></div><p class=\"miniapp\"></p></div></div>  <div id=\"facsimile-images\"><h2>Facsimile Images</h2></div>  <div id=\"apparatus\"><h4>Apparatus criticus</h4><ul><li><span>  <span>text of IG</span>  </span></li></ul></div>  <div id=\"translation\"><h2> translation</h2><p class=\"translation-author\">  </p><p>  </p></div>  <div id=\"commentary\"><h2>commentary</h2>  <p>The text is described as very lightly inscribed, and Kaibel is sceptical of its genuineness, since other stones which he saw in the collection of Lipari were false. Manganaro follows Kaibel's suggested conjectures, with the naming of an Emperor and filiation in the opening lines, suggested to be in the genitive preceded by ὑπὲρ σωτηρίας (for the safety of), and the benefactor being a Septic[ius], perhaps responsible for the construction of a [palae]stran, with a second individual, a Flavius, also involved. </p>  </div>  <div id=\"bibliography\"><h2>bibliography</h2>  <ul><li> Kaibel 1890 <a href=\"https://clio.columbia.edu/catalog/6873760\" target=\"_blank\">275</a>  <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072</a></li><li> Manganaro 1988 45 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001427\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001427</a></li><li> Wilson 1990 169, 381 n.72 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001509\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001509</a></li></ul>  <ul><li></li></ul>  </div>  <div id=\"handnote\"> Line 1     Interlineation line 1 to 2     </div><div id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. </div>",
  "divs": [
    {
